      • open

        public static TitanGraph open(String shortcutOrFile)
        Opens a TitanGraph database.

        If the argument points to a configuration file, the configuration file is loaded to configure the Titan graph If the string argument is a configuration short-cut, then the short-cut is parsed and used to configure the returned Titan graph.

        A configuration short-cut is of the form: [STORAGE_BACKEND_NAME]:[DIRECTORY_OR_HOST]

        Parameters:
        shortcutOrFile - Configuration file name or configuration short-cut
        Returns:
        Titan graph database configured according to the provided configuration
        See Also:
        "Configuration" manual chapter, Configuration Reference

      • build

        public static TitanFactory.Builder build()
        Returns a TitanFactory.Builder that allows to set the configuration options for opening a Titan graph database.

        In the builder, the configuration options for the graph can be set individually. Once all options are configured, the graph can be opened with TitanFactory.Builder.open().
